http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Four-year-old-raped-by-teenager/article14015491.ece

A four-year-old girl was allegedly raped by a 14-year-old boy at Atchutapuram village in Aswaraopet mandal on Thursday night.According to police sources, the shocking incident took place at around 8.30 p.m. on Thursday night when the girl was playing in the street abutting her house along with some children.A 14-year-old boy of the same village allegedly whisked away the girl to a secluded spot and raped her in a parked autorickshaw near a farm on the periphery of the village.He allegedly abandoned the girl near her house and fled from the spot.Alerted by the local residents, the mother of the victim rushed to the place and found her daughter bleeding profusely.The relatives of the victim alerted the local police about the shocking incident and shifted the girl to the Primary Health Centre in Aswaraopet the same night.The condition of the girl is stated to be stable.The Aswaraopet police registered a case and are investigating.